From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 29 Nov 2025 15:33:25 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] pci: cadence: sky1: Enable WiFi PCIe controller (pcie_x2_rc)

Remove temporary debug code that restricted PCIe probing to only the
NVMe controller. Enable pcie_x2_rc (M.2 E-Key) for WiFi support.

DTS changes:
- Enable pcie_x2_rc with proper reset-gpios and power supply
- Configure pinctrl for WiFi PCIe lane

Driver changes:
- Remove temporary skip logic that blocked secondary controllers

Tested with Realtek RTL8852BE WiFi 6 adapter on Radxa Orion O6.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1-orion-o6.dts |  8 ++++++--
 drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c | 11 -----------
 2 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 13 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1-orion-o6.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1-orion-o6.dts
index 7fca32ccc5b5..4e7578a4f0ec 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1-orion-o6.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1-orion-o6.dts
@@ -2087,9 +2087,13 @@ &pcie_x4_rc {
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
-/* M.2 E-Key - disabled to avoid resource conflict during boot */
+/* M.2 E-Key (WiFi) */
 &pcie_x2_rc {
-	status = "disabled";
+	pinctrl-names = "default";
+	pinctrl-0 = <&pinctrl_pcie_x2_rc>;
+	reset-gpios = <&s5_gpio0 4 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
+	vcc-pcie-supply = <&vdd_3v3_pcie>;
+	status = "okay";
 };
 
 /* 5GBE-1 - disabled to avoid resource conflict during boot */
diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c b/drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c
index 993ff61350b3..efc5f1f08b71 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c
@@ -2326,17 +2326,6 @@ static int sky1_pcie_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	dev_info(dev, "%s starting!\n", __func__);
 
-	/* TEMPORARY: Only allow NVMe controller (a070000) to probe.
-	 * Other controllers cause resource conflicts during bring-up.
-	 */
-	{
-		struct resource *res = platform_get_resource(pdev, IORESOURCE_MEM, 0);
-		if (res && res->start != 0x0a070000) {
-			dev_info(dev, "Skipping secondary controller at %pR\n", res);
-			return -ENODEV;
-		}
-	}
-
 	pcie = devm_kzalloc(dev, sizeof(*pcie), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!pcie)
 		return -ENOMEM;
